<h3>BRANCHES OF ASTRONOMY </h3>

<section id="boxes">
<div class="container">
<div class="box">
<img src="astrobiology.jpg">
          <h4>ASTROBIOLOGY </h4>
          <p>Astrobiology is the study of life in the universe, including its origins, evolution, and future. It's an interdisciplinary field that combines astronomy, biology, geology, and planetary science. </p>
        </div>

        <div class="box">
          <img src="planetary science.jpg">
          <h4>PLANETARY SCIENCE</h4>
          <p>Planetary science is the study of planets, moons, and other celestial bodies in our solar system. It's an interdisciplinary field that combines astronomy, geology, physics, and more.  </p>
        </div>
        <div class="box">
          <img src="astrometry.jpg">
          <h4>ASTROMETRY</h4>
          <p>Astrometry is the science of measuring the positions and movements of celestial objects. It's a field of astronomy that involves precise measurements of stars and planets in the sky.  </p>
        </div>
      </div>

<aside id="sidebar">
<div class="dark">
<h3>ASTRONOMY VS ASTROLOGY</h3>
What's the difference? 
Astronomy 
<ol>
<li>A scientific discipline that studies the universe beyond Earth's atmosphere</li>
<li>Astronomers study the positions, motions, and properties of celestial objects</li>
<li>Astronomers use research and observation to base their studies</li></ol>

Astrology
<ol>
<li>A non-scientific belief system that uses the positions of celestial objects to predict or explain human behavior</li>
<li>Astrology is considered a pseudoscience because it has no scientific basis</li>
<li>Astrology is a form of personal life guide</li>
</div>
</aside>
</div>
</section>


